23:31.844 --> 23:33.744
You felt like...
Like an outcast.

23:33.746 --> 23:35.079
It was all of a sudden,

23:35.081 --> 23:37.181
everybody was, like,
Team Juliette.

23:37.183 --> 23:39.150
At least Cara
was with me.

23:39.152 --> 23:42.186
I literally have no idea
what I would have done

23:42.188 --> 23:44.622
if she wasn't there.

23:44.624 --> 23:47.091
Come on, Murray.
Have a seat.

23:48.261 --> 23:50.261
That's a good boy!
Come here.

23:50.263 --> 23:51.829
Um, I think

23:51.831 --> 23:55.099
Juliette thinks
Cara's intentions are bad.

23:55.101 --> 23:57.701
She thinks I'm purposely
trying to, like,

23:57.703 --> 23:58.702
hurt her feelings

23:58.704 --> 24:00.337
by bringing Cara around.

24:00.339 --> 24:01.972
Well, I hope
you're gonna have

24:01.974 --> 24:03.841
a discussion with Juliette
about it.

24:03.843 --> 24:06.343
But if I don't care,
why would I wanna talk to her?

24:06.345 --> 24:09.346
Because you don't want her
to continue to do this.

24:09.348 --> 24:10.614
♪♪

24:10.616 --> 24:12.216
I think it's time
to start your future,

24:12.218 --> 24:13.984
start a profession.

24:13.986 --> 24:16.720
I mean, you don't want
all this drama going on.

24:16.722 --> 24:19.623
I think
it's just ridiculous

24:19.625 --> 24:21.659
that you girls--
you're in your 20s now,

24:21.661 --> 24:22.993
you're not in high school
any more--

24:22.995 --> 24:26.230
how immature you guys
are all acting.

24:26.232 --> 24:28.499
Y'all just need
to grow up.

24:28.501 --> 24:31.469
♪♪

24:31.471 --> 24:32.636
It's really hard
to wanna have

24:32.638 --> 24:34.839
a heart-to-heart conversation

24:34.841 --> 24:37.808
with somebody talking really,
really, nasty about you.

24:37.810 --> 24:40.945
What kind of friend is that?
Well, I think it's time
to have a discussion with her

24:40.947 --> 24:44.415
and figure it out
and, you know, move on.

24:44.417 --> 24:46.050
(sighing)

24:46.052 --> 24:47.017
I don't know.

24:47.019 --> 24:49.086
Have you thought
anything more about

24:49.088 --> 24:50.821
getting into
the real estate business

24:50.823 --> 24:52.490
like the rest
of your family is?

24:52.492 --> 24:54.859
That's what I should have
went to school for.

24:54.861 --> 24:57.027
I just don't want to
feel pressured by anyone.

24:57.029 --> 24:59.930
Well, you're the one that
brings on your own pressure.

24:59.932 --> 25:01.332
Nobody is pressuring you.

25:01.334 --> 25:02.500
They-- mmm...

25:02.502 --> 25:03.934
have you met our family?
No, they don't.

25:03.936 --> 25:05.536
Yes, they do.
I know our family
very well.

25:05.538 --> 25:06.704
They do.

25:06.706 --> 25:08.172
I'm not getting rich
but I'm happy,

25:08.174 --> 25:10.007
and that's all
that matters, Chloe,

25:10.009 --> 25:11.709
is to find something...
I know.

25:11.711 --> 25:13.711
...you're happy with.

25:13.713 --> 25:16.213
You need to focus
on your future.

25:16.215 --> 25:17.982
Yeah, we'll see.

25:19.752 --> 25:22.887
♪♪

25:35.701 --> 25:37.368
What's up?

25:37.370 --> 25:38.736
Hey.

25:38.738 --> 25:41.505
How are ya?
What's going on?

25:41.507 --> 25:43.641
(Juliette)
Everyone thinks Pauly
should be a bigger man

25:43.643 --> 25:44.775
and apologize to Jared...

25:44.777 --> 25:46.310
Who the (bleep)
are you?!

25:46.312 --> 25:48.178
(Juliette)
...but Pauly cares about
one thing only:

25:48.180 --> 25:49.413
(excited chatter)

25:49.415 --> 25:52.249
...defending Alex's honor.

25:52.251 --> 25:53.350
It's a bit much.

25:55.755 --> 25:59.189
I kinda wanted to amend
this whole situation

25:59.191 --> 26:00.958
before it gets,
I guess,

26:00.960 --> 26:02.960
more out of control.
Right.

26:02.962 --> 26:04.895
What happened wasn't okay
on either side,

26:04.897 --> 26:06.630
but especially wasn't okay

26:06.632 --> 26:08.999
for you to show up
to Alex's birthday

26:09.001 --> 26:11.302
and start
all this trouble.

26:11.304 --> 26:14.705
♪♪

26:14.707 --> 26:17.741
I've been gone
for seven years.

26:17.743 --> 26:20.010
I've been through
hell and back.

26:20.012 --> 26:21.946
I get it if he has
tension with me forever,

26:21.948 --> 26:23.547
but I don't think
I have to be like,

26:23.549 --> 26:24.982
"Oh, if I show up
to his party,

26:24.984 --> 26:27.785
am I gonna get (bleep) jumped
for no (bleep) reason?"

26:27.787 --> 26:29.853
You have to take
some responsibility

26:29.855 --> 26:32.122
for what you did.

26:32.124 --> 26:34.658
Why show up to someone's
birthday party
you don't like?

26:34.660 --> 26:36.493
I'm here,

26:36.495 --> 26:38.028
it's my
first summer back,

26:38.030 --> 26:40.431
I wanna have a good time just
as much as anyone else does.

26:40.433 --> 26:41.699
It was just
really disrespectful

26:41.701 --> 26:43.200
and it's a bad idea,

26:43.202 --> 26:45.703
because Alex is the most
popular kid in this town.

26:45.705 --> 26:47.237
You being friends with Alex

26:47.239 --> 26:49.440
is something that
you should strive for.

26:49.442 --> 26:51.241
'Cause he doesn't need
to be friends with you.

26:54.814 --> 26:57.348
I mean, I wouldn't go
as far to say that, but...

26:57.350 --> 26:59.183
(laughs)

26:59.185 --> 27:01.652
♪♪

27:01.654 --> 27:02.820
I feel like we should
be able to be

27:02.822 --> 27:04.088
in the same place
at the same time.

27:04.090 --> 27:06.156
Like, everyone's drunk,
and (bleep) happens,

27:06.158 --> 27:08.726
but... should that
have happened? No.

27:08.728 --> 27:12.029
Like maybe pull me
to the side, and be like,
"Yo, like, just leave."

27:12.031 --> 27:15.065
That's fine.
Like, we're adults now.

27:15.067 --> 27:16.867
This is...

27:19.238 --> 27:23.307
I did strike you,
and I don't think
anybody should get jumped.

27:23.309 --> 27:27.011
If you truly came there
not to cause trouble,

27:27.013 --> 27:28.278
then I apologize.

27:28.280 --> 27:29.747
It looks like you're
back in town,

27:29.749 --> 27:31.048
and we're gonna have
to see each other,

27:31.050 --> 27:33.183
so I'd like to nip this
in the bud,

27:33.185 --> 27:36.887
but I think this ends
with you and Alex
on the same page.

27:36.889 --> 27:39.857
I'm not gonna come up here
and blatantly disrespect him,

27:39.859 --> 27:42.159
or go at his throat,
but I'm not gonna, like,

27:42.161 --> 27:43.727
you know, bow down
to, like, someone else.

27:43.729 --> 27:45.129
Well, that's just the thing,

27:45.131 --> 27:46.797
it seems like you guys
are clashing because

27:46.799 --> 27:48.432
you refuse to bow down.

27:48.434 --> 27:51.969
♪♪

27:53.739 --> 27:57.207
♪ Whoa oh oh oh oh ♪

27:57.209 --> 27:59.276
♪ I'm a one-woman army ♪

27:59.278 --> 28:01.045
(Brandon)
Chloe's here.

28:01.047 --> 28:02.546
What's up, Chloe?
How you doing?

28:02.548 --> 28:04.615
Sorry we got there
so late the other night.

28:04.617 --> 28:06.083
No, no.
The traffic was so bad.

28:06.085 --> 28:07.217
Don't worry about it.
I understand.

28:07.219 --> 28:08.719
I wasn't disappointed
about that.

28:08.721 --> 28:10.054
♪ I'm a one-woman army ♪

28:10.056 --> 28:12.189
Let me introduce you to Cara.
Yes.

28:12.191 --> 28:15.526
Hi, I'm Madisson.
Nice to meet you, Cara.

28:15.528 --> 28:16.827
This is Kelsey.

28:16.829 --> 28:18.462
(Kelsey)
Nice to see you.

28:18.464 --> 28:20.564
You, too.

28:20.566 --> 28:23.701
You gonna say hi or no?

28:23.703 --> 28:25.169
I don't have much
to say to you.

28:25.171 --> 28:26.637
Do you have a lot to say?

28:26.639 --> 28:28.072
No, I have
absolutely nothing.

28:28.074 --> 28:29.606
I just thought I'd say hi
and be respectful.

28:29.608 --> 28:31.408
Yeah, I'm not like
into fake stuff.

28:31.410 --> 28:33.811
So it's like if you have
nothing to say other than hi,

28:33.813 --> 28:36.947
then it's like why say hi?

28:36.949 --> 28:38.215
(Kelsey)
So why is she
really pissed at me

28:38.217 --> 28:39.783
and completely fine
with you?

28:39.785 --> 28:42.152
It's my impression
that she...

28:42.154 --> 28:44.755
felt attacked by you.
And...

28:44.757 --> 28:46.290
I was...

28:46.292 --> 28:47.357
Why do you guys
always fight,

28:47.359 --> 28:48.859
like everywhere
you go?

28:48.861 --> 28:50.761
My main thing
that I'm really upset with

28:50.763 --> 28:54.031
is I don't want to have problems
with anyone in the group

28:54.033 --> 28:56.133
because of Juliette
and I's issues.

28:56.135 --> 28:58.802
Juliette and I's issues are
Juliette and I's issues.

28:58.804 --> 29:00.904
And the other night,
I just felt like

29:00.906 --> 29:04.074
every single person
was against me,

29:04.076 --> 29:06.176
and I just didn't understand.
Okay.

29:06.178 --> 29:08.712
So, yes, that night,
I feel like the right thing

29:08.714 --> 29:12.282
was to back up Juliette,
because once I understood
the whole, entire situation--

29:12.284 --> 29:13.684
When you talk so much (bleep)
about her and you--

29:13.686 --> 29:16.120
I agree! Like, yes,
Juliette and I have our (bleep).

29:16.122 --> 29:18.355
Yes, I (bleep) have had
so much (bleep) with Juliette.

29:18.357 --> 29:20.257
There's been times I (bleep)
wanna kill Juliette.

29:20.259 --> 29:22.259
So you would
take Juliette's side,
who's not your friend,

29:22.261 --> 29:23.460
when I've been
a friend to you.

29:27.199 --> 29:29.099
Stick up for me
if the time comes.

29:29.101 --> 29:32.503
Course I will.
Like, say something
mean to Cara.

29:32.505 --> 29:34.671
You have to.

29:34.673 --> 29:36.006
Oh, my God.

29:39.478 --> 29:40.277
♪♪

29:40.279 --> 29:41.912
You won't be able
to get it.

29:41.914 --> 29:44.214
(shrieks and laughs)

29:44.216 --> 29:46.049
So I have
questions.

29:46.051 --> 29:47.217
What's up?

29:47.219 --> 29:48.852
I wanna know
how you guys met.

29:48.854 --> 29:50.187
We exchanged Snapchat.

29:50.189 --> 29:52.790
Did you sleep together
on the first date?

29:52.792 --> 29:54.224
Chloe!
Jesus Christmas.

29:54.226 --> 29:56.794
It was like
the first couple dates.

29:56.796 --> 29:57.895
So the first date.

29:57.897 --> 29:59.229
Whatcha-- no.

29:59.231 --> 30:00.597
(laughter and chatter)

30:00.599 --> 30:02.332
It's like, yeah.

30:02.334 --> 30:04.334
♪♪

30:04.336 --> 30:06.403
♪ Okay, hooked up,
let me get my words right ♪

30:06.405 --> 30:08.939
♪ Sound kinda crazy, I been
loving you from first sight ♪

30:08.941 --> 30:11.408
What up?

30:12.778 --> 30:14.077
How are you feeling?

30:15.948 --> 30:17.481
You just came in
at a good time.

30:17.483 --> 30:19.082
(Jared)
Why, is the party
getting started?

30:19.084 --> 30:20.450
What have you
been up to?

30:20.452 --> 30:22.119
My brother's in
the Air Force, by the way.

30:22.121 --> 30:23.687
Good for him.
Yes, yeah.

30:23.689 --> 30:25.589
He's the smart one.
Yeah, he's
the smart one.

30:25.591 --> 30:26.657
And then
I got the looks.

30:26.659 --> 30:28.458
So it, like, worked out
in my benefit.

30:28.460 --> 30:30.127
That's how I feel
in my family, too.

30:30.129 --> 30:32.095
Yeah, it's just like...
it's fine.
(indistinct).

30:32.097 --> 30:33.130
So I know Jared
from high school.

30:33.132 --> 30:34.531
Mm-hmm.
Like, I dated him.

30:35.534 --> 30:37.167
But, like, he, like,
wanted to get,

30:37.169 --> 30:38.869
like, way too serious
way too fast.

30:38.871 --> 30:40.938
What do you mean,
like he just like asked you
out really quickly?

30:40.940 --> 30:43.173
Like, he discussed marriage.

30:43.175 --> 30:45.075
He's (bleep)
multiple of my friends.

30:45.077 --> 30:47.544
Like, we've known
each other for years.

30:47.546 --> 30:49.146
Even when
I was in boot camp,

30:49.148 --> 30:51.148
Madisson was sending me
those lingerie pics.

30:51.150 --> 30:53.450
Like, he gave me like
this promise necklace--

30:53.452 --> 30:54.918
So he proposed to you.
Not really.

30:54.920 --> 30:56.753
But like he insinuated
that like if we were gonna

30:56.755 --> 30:58.522
continue this relationship,
it was going to end--

30:58.524 --> 30:59.890
So what was your guys'
relationship?

30:59.892 --> 31:01.925
It ended after that.
I was like I-- no.

31:01.927 --> 31:03.260
When you came
back into town,

31:03.262 --> 31:05.262
you two were hooking up,
and that's when--

31:05.264 --> 31:06.730
Every time, so, I mean,
even when I--

31:06.732 --> 31:09.299
Oh, every time?
So I just have one question.

31:09.301 --> 31:12.669
Have you slept with her
more than two times?

31:12.671 --> 31:13.837
More than 10?

31:13.839 --> 31:14.972
Yeah.

31:14.974 --> 31:16.106
More than 20?

31:16.108 --> 31:17.541
Mm...

31:17.543 --> 31:18.842
In between 15 and 20?

31:18.844 --> 31:20.010
Yeah. 15 and 20.

31:20.012 --> 31:21.178
Okay.

31:22.114 --> 31:23.747
Take a drink.

31:27.286 --> 31:31.288
(Juliette)
So ridiculous that Chloe would
show up to the bar with Cara.

31:31.290 --> 31:33.290
She's free to do
whatever she wants.

31:33.292 --> 31:34.758
Like, I don't know
what else--

31:34.760 --> 31:36.526
Just annoying that,
like, I always have

31:36.528 --> 31:38.161
to deal with your
ex-girlfriends.

31:38.163 --> 31:39.696
And here's another one.

31:39.698 --> 31:41.465
She just does such bad
things to her friends.

31:41.467 --> 31:43.300
You just need to learn to just
give her no reaction,

31:43.302 --> 31:44.768
'cause that's exactly
what she wants.

31:44.770 --> 31:46.837
How am I supposed to not
react to that situation?

31:46.839 --> 31:49.940
By having trust in me
and knowing I don't give
a crap about her.

31:49.942 --> 31:53.377
Yeah, but I hate that girl.
Like, I don't want her
around you.

31:53.379 --> 31:54.811
Juliet--
I don't know.

31:54.813 --> 31:57.547
I don't know how many
times I have to tell you,

31:57.549 --> 32:00.017
I don't care
about Cara at all.

32:00.019 --> 32:02.152
Chloe is trying
to get between us,

32:02.154 --> 32:04.388
and every time you fall
for her traps,

32:04.390 --> 32:06.857
it's just gonna put us
in a worse situation.

32:06.859 --> 32:10.661
She goes home all happy,
like, "Ooh, it worked."
Da-da-da-da-da.

32:10.663 --> 32:12.696
Like, Cara,
you're my best friend."

32:12.698 --> 32:16.800
Probably Cara doesn't even
know why she's being invited
to these places.

32:16.802 --> 32:20.537
I can guarantee it's to
piss you off, which it does,
which it does.

32:20.539 --> 32:22.172
And in return,
it pisses me off,

32:22.174 --> 32:23.540
'cause I have
to deal with it.

32:23.542 --> 32:25.008
You know, it's like
you're getting mad at me

32:25.010 --> 32:26.376
for being upset about this.

32:26.378 --> 32:28.645
Oh, my God.
I'm allowed to be mad.

32:28.647 --> 32:30.380
I don't wanna get woken up
to being yelled at

32:30.382 --> 32:32.549
for something
I've nothing to do with.

32:32.551 --> 32:34.084
(sighs)

32:34.086 --> 32:35.552
That's what I--

32:35.554 --> 32:37.721
You need to stick up for me
if the time comes.

32:37.723 --> 32:41.224
Of course I will.
Like say something
mean to Cara.

32:41.226 --> 32:43.527
You have to.

32:43.529 --> 32:45.963
Tell her she's psycho
for even coming.

32:45.965 --> 32:49.533
Just turn the shoulder
and don't play
their game, dude.

32:49.535 --> 32:51.535
(sighs)
All right.

32:51.537 --> 32:52.936
You just need
to chill, dude.

32:52.938 --> 32:55.539
You're just-- you just
have no, like, idea

32:55.541 --> 32:58.342
how this ever will feel,
is the issue.

33:07.419 --> 33:09.152
Why are all your friends
turning against you?

33:09.154 --> 33:10.387
I don't know.
Tell me.

33:10.389 --> 33:12.389
I took Juliette's side
for one night!

33:12.391 --> 33:15.058
I'm done. I'll literally
break your (bleep) face again

33:15.060 --> 33:17.694
and not feel bad about it.

33:19.298 --> 33:21.064
♪ We can do this every night ♪

33:21.066 --> 33:24.701
♪ You can be
my ride or die ♪

33:24.703 --> 33:27.804
♪ We're gonna live this way
every day ♪

33:27.806 --> 33:29.473
♪♪

33:29.475 --> 33:31.141
What's up, ladies?
Hi!

33:31.143 --> 33:33.076
I'm gonna go
make a drink.

33:33.078 --> 33:34.511
Hey, bring me
something.

33:34.513 --> 33:36.580
♪♪

33:36.582 --> 33:38.248
Looking good,
as always.

33:38.250 --> 33:39.716
Oh, thank you.
I miss you.

33:43.322 --> 33:46.356
Yep.
(laughing)

33:46.358 --> 33:49.292
You don't have to nervously
dip your feet in the sand,
either.

33:49.294 --> 33:52.295
No, my--
my toes are cold.

33:52.297 --> 33:55.732
It's good see familiar
faces back here, 'cause...

33:57.102 --> 33:58.902
Very familiar!

34:00.205 --> 34:01.605
Would you wanna
go out sometime?

34:06.311 --> 34:08.045
I don't know.
You don't know?

34:08.047 --> 34:09.479
I don't know, I think...

34:09.481 --> 34:12.049
I have to kind of
feel out this thing

34:12.051 --> 34:13.183
that I have going on.

34:13.185 --> 34:15.218
But, um...

34:15.220 --> 34:17.320
Definitely gonna
be seeing you around!

34:17.322 --> 34:19.689
Yeah. I mean,
I guess so.

34:21.226 --> 34:23.026
You just gotta just
straight up.

34:23.028 --> 34:25.929
Oh, thank you.
Like that. Right.

34:25.931 --> 34:30.767
♪♪

34:30.769 --> 34:33.970
♪ They call me wild child,
so what you heard about me ♪

34:33.972 --> 34:37.474
♪ Dangerous wild child,
I know you heard about me ♪

34:37.476 --> 34:40.944
♪ Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah,
let's start a riot ♪

34:40.946 --> 34:44.681
(Juliette)
Last year, me, Amanda
and Chloe were besties.

34:44.683 --> 34:45.849
Cheers to that.

34:45.851 --> 34:47.851
But after the whole
broken nose thing...

34:47.853 --> 34:49.186
Oops.

34:49.188 --> 34:51.021
...and after the scenes Chloe
made at Alex's party...

34:51.023 --> 34:53.123
Of course you brought Cara.
You-- she knew.

34:53.125 --> 34:54.491
...and Brandon's show...

34:54.493 --> 34:56.359
Stop!
Don't push me, honey.

34:56.361 --> 34:57.761
Don't put your hands on me.

34:57.763 --> 34:59.162
Don't talk to me about
my relationship!

34:59.164 --> 35:00.897
...Amanda was almost
as over Chloe

35:00.899 --> 35:02.299
as I was.

35:02.301 --> 35:03.900
(Chloe)
So, Amanda...

35:03.902 --> 35:05.402
Chloe.

35:05.404 --> 35:08.972
Honestly,
we need to talk.

35:08.974 --> 35:11.007
You brought her.
You knew you were bringing her
to stir the pot.

35:11.009 --> 35:12.676
Why is she
stirring the pot?
You know why you're here.

35:12.678 --> 35:13.977
These are my friends.
This is our friend group.

35:13.979 --> 35:15.946
We all support--
But these are
your friends,

35:15.948 --> 35:17.314
so am I not your friend?

35:17.316 --> 35:18.381
I never
(bleep) said that!

35:18.383 --> 35:19.683
That's what you
just acted like.

35:19.685 --> 35:21.184
Why are all your friends
turning against you?

35:21.186 --> 35:22.519
