they do not trust me,

36:25.450 --> 36:26.983
it's them telling me
they're not my friend.

36:26.985 --> 36:28.752
Whatev-- how do you feel
about your friends

36:28.754 --> 36:30.120
telling me
they don't trust you?

36:30.122 --> 36:31.288
No! They don't
do that.

36:31.290 --> 36:32.489
Cara, so why--
they don't do that,

36:32.491 --> 36:33.990
so why would I
sit there, Cara?

36:33.992 --> 36:35.525
No, you're right.
Give me one reason
I sit there.

36:35.527 --> 36:36.760
You're right.
Can I just say something?

36:36.762 --> 36:38.128
I was just there
and I was like,

36:38.130 --> 36:39.663
"Chloe has only ever
been there for me..."

36:39.665 --> 36:40.830
Okay, this is--
understand this situation.

36:40.832 --> 36:42.165
No, Amanda, you said
you don't trust me.

36:42.167 --> 36:43.333
No, I don't--
no, I don't!

36:43.335 --> 36:45.101
You're not my friend.
You just said

36:45.103 --> 36:46.903
none of you trust me!
I said I don't trust you!

36:46.905 --> 36:48.805
Are you surprised
I don't trust you?

36:48.807 --> 36:50.340
Are you surprised?
Are you surprised

36:50.342 --> 36:52.008
I don't want to break
my nose again?

36:52.010 --> 36:53.276
(chuckles)

36:53.278 --> 36:55.278
That (bleep) about to
pop off though, for real.

36:55.280 --> 36:57.914
Go ahead and say it again,
that it was my (bleep) fault

36:57.916 --> 37:00.016
that you got
your (bleep) nose broke!

37:00.018 --> 37:01.785
It was your fault.
You didn't slap me
in the face

37:01.787 --> 37:03.153
right before it?
It was your fault.

37:03.155 --> 37:04.721
You're dumb. Leave.
Nobody likes you here.

37:04.723 --> 37:07.357
Go. I'll literally break
your (bleep) face again

37:07.359 --> 37:09.326
and not feel bad
about it.
That's why I was leaving.

37:09.328 --> 37:10.527
And you wonder why
I want to leave?

37:10.529 --> 37:11.728
'Cause you're a (bleep)
dumb bitch

37:11.730 --> 37:13.163
and nobody (bleep)
trusts you!

37:13.165 --> 37:15.999
I'll (bleep) break it again
you dumb (bleep)!

37:16.001 --> 37:18.802
(Chloe crying)

37:18.804 --> 37:22.906
They're all attacking me.
Like, I don't understand.

37:22.908 --> 37:26.876
♪♪

37:34.119 --> 37:36.620
This is not how I want
to start my morning, Juliette.

37:36.622 --> 37:37.821
Like...
(sighs)

37:37.823 --> 37:40.757
It's just, you should be
a little mad

37:40.759 --> 37:42.225
about Cara
being around too.

37:42.227 --> 37:44.594
Like, I feel like
I was the only one
that was angry,

37:44.596 --> 37:45.996
and you kinda
were just like

37:45.998 --> 37:48.031
basking in the glory
that your ex is there

37:48.033 --> 37:49.499
and your new girlfriend's
there and, like,

37:49.501 --> 37:51.968
everyone wants you, right?

37:51.970 --> 37:55.171
Alex, I don't think you get
how much it sucks

37:55.173 --> 37:58.174
that you've slept with
all these people I know.

37:58.176 --> 38:00.910
It's a constant reminder,
and now Cara is here

38:00.912 --> 38:03.880
